main event: On May 25, 1957, three circular objects were observed in Elkhorn, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The objects were red and white in color and comparable in size to commercial airliner lights., The observation lasted for two minutes., Two additional observers reported seeing only a white object and thought it was a flare., The source of the sighting was civilian., The report classified the observation as ground-visual.
witness description: two were civilian observers, one might be inferred from the report
